1
00:00:11,667 --> 00:00:12,700
<i>- Call the nurse!
- Nurse!</i>

2
00:00:12,833 --> 00:00:14,533
<i>Ma'am, I really don't know
anything about that.</i>

3
00:00:14,667 --> 00:00:16,900
<i>For example, if someone
wanted to switch out</i>

4
00:00:17,033 --> 00:00:18,767
<i>the medication meant
for a patient...</i>

5
00:00:18,900 --> 00:00:21,433
<i>We leave the medication
at the nurse's station.</i>

6
00:00:21,567 --> 00:00:23,033
<i>We didn't see anything strange
earlier either.</i>

7
00:00:23,167 --> 00:00:24,400
<i>Robles, have you seen anything?</i>

8
00:00:24,533 --> 00:00:25,767
<i>No, I didn't see
anything earlier.</i>

9
00:00:25,900 --> 00:00:27,733
<i> Doctor, we need you here.</i>

10
00:00:27,867 --> 00:00:29,233
<i>Was this really how he looked
when he died?</i>

11
00:00:29,367 --> 00:00:30,467
<i> After his seizure,</i>

12
00:00:30,600 --> 00:00:32,167
<i>it looked like he went through
intense pain</i>

13
00:00:32,300 --> 00:00:33,433
<i> and his whole body stiffened.</i>

14
00:00:33,600 --> 00:00:36,333
<i>Unless someone
didn't want him to talk.</i>

15
00:00:36,467 --> 00:00:37,533
<i> Check the address first.</i>

16
00:00:37,667 --> 00:00:39,100
<i> We might find something there.</i>

17
00:00:39,233 --> 00:00:40,233
<i> Don't arrest me.</i>

18
00:00:40,367 --> 00:00:41,167
<i> You're here</i>

19
00:00:41,300 --> 00:00:42,267
<i>because of that kidnapping,
right?</i>

20
00:00:43,433 --> 00:00:44,467
<i>I can't imagine
the kind of struggle</i>

21
00:00:44,600 --> 00:00:45,500
<i> you're going through,</i>

22
00:00:45,633 --> 00:00:47,133
<i>but I know that
you need justice...</i>

23
00:00:47,267 --> 00:00:48,600
<i> for your own closure.</i>

24
00:00:48,733 --> 00:00:50,767
<i>I guess this is
where you tell me</i>

25
00:00:50,900 --> 00:00:52,467
<i> what you want in return...</i>

26
00:00:52,600 --> 00:00:53,967
<i> for the favor you did for me.</i>

27
00:00:54,100 --> 00:00:56,867
<i>One of the kidnappers you
brought to the hospital,</i>

28
00:00:57,000 --> 00:00:58,633
<i>that's Sonny, he's my boyfriend.</i>

29
00:00:58,767 --> 00:01:00,467
<i>Lieutenant Conde, what's
happening?</i>

30
00:01:03,933 --> 00:01:07,600
The subject's back arch is very
pronounced,

31
00:01:08,100 --> 00:01:11,033
especially that strange
green tint on his face.

32
00:01:13,033 --> 00:01:15,467
The rigor mortis
is already advanced

33
00:01:15,600 --> 00:01:17,467
considering his time of death.

34
00:01:17,600 --> 00:01:21,633
Clear signs of poisoning
or a tetanus infection.

35
00:01:21,767 --> 00:01:24,267
I didn't find any other
injection marks

36
00:01:24,400 --> 00:01:26,600
aside from the IV access mark.

37
00:01:26,733 --> 00:01:31,133
We'll collect a sample using
vitreous humor aspiration.

38
00:01:37,533 --> 00:01:40,200
Sonny Ocampo is the name of our
kidnapper, Chief.

39
00:01:40,333 --> 00:01:41,467
Okay, Lieutenant Conde.

40
00:01:41,633 --> 00:01:42,933
Just keep the line open

41
00:01:43,067 --> 00:01:45,633
so we can listen in
on the interrogation.

42
00:01:46,500 --> 00:01:47,900
Yes, Sir.

43
00:01:49,100 --> 00:01:50,900
Garcia! Robles!

44
00:01:51,033 --> 00:01:55,267
Run Sonny Ocampo's
name through our system.

45
00:01:55,400 --> 00:01:58,800
But, Sir, aren't we the ones
assigned to this case?

46
00:01:58,933 --> 00:01:59,733
Shouldn't we be the ones

47
00:01:59,867 --> 00:02:01,467
interrogating Selena?

48
00:02:01,600 --> 00:02:02,900
Seriously, Garcia?

49
00:02:03,033 --> 00:02:05,600
After all that slacking earlier?

50
00:02:05,733 --> 00:02:07,133
Get moving!

51
00:02:07,267 --> 00:02:08,533
The Mayor just stepped out
to eat.

52
00:02:08,667 --> 00:02:12,567
When he returns, we better have
something to show him.

53
00:02:17,100 --> 00:02:18,733
Look at that, Garcia.

54
00:02:18,867 --> 00:02:21,333
You were still making bets
earlier...

55
00:02:21,467 --> 00:02:23,400
and now we've got nothing.

56
00:02:25,333 --> 00:02:29,233
Selena Madrigal Gomez, correct?

57
00:02:31,167 --> 00:02:34,267
How long have you
and Sonny Ocampo been together?

58
00:02:35,900 --> 00:02:37,767
It's been a while now.

59
00:02:43,433 --> 00:02:46,733
Here, we've got pictures.

60
00:02:47,200 --> 00:02:48,800
There.

61
00:03:02,567 --> 00:03:05,400
Sir, I'm not a suspect, right?

62
00:03:05,533 --> 00:03:09,267
That depends, if you're actually
involved in the crime.

63
00:03:09,400 --> 00:03:12,133
What do you know about Sonny's
activities?

64
00:03:12,267 --> 00:03:14,633
Okay, here's the truth,

65
00:03:15,267 --> 00:03:16,800
I knew that...

66
00:03:17,400 --> 00:03:19,867
I knew that he was involved
in some criminal activities,

67
00:03:20,000 --> 00:03:22,700
but I had no idea
about the deatils

68
00:03:22,867 --> 00:03:25,267
of what they actually did in
their work.

69
00:03:25,400 --> 00:03:26,733
I only found out last week

70
00:03:26,867 --> 00:03:28,000
about the kidnapping.

71
00:03:28,133 --> 00:03:29,500
I didn't even know

72
00:03:29,633 --> 00:03:31,767
the Mayor's child
was their target.

73
00:03:31,900 --> 00:03:32,900
Listen to me...

74
00:03:33,033 --> 00:03:34,333
I warned him.

75
00:03:34,467 --> 00:03:36,433
I told him to stop.

76
00:03:36,567 --> 00:03:38,033
He wouldn't listen.

77
00:03:38,167 --> 00:03:40,700
I even begged him to change.

78
00:03:40,833 --> 00:03:41,967
I don't know...

79
00:03:42,100 --> 00:03:44,300
the voice of that demon got to
him stronger than mine.

80
00:03:44,900 --> 00:03:47,200
Demon?
Who's the demon?

81
00:03:47,333 --> 00:03:49,200
His boss.

82
00:04:21,367 --> 00:04:23,433
Yes, Sonny Ocampo.

83
00:04:23,567 --> 00:04:27,133
Get every piece of information
you can on him.

84
00:04:27,567 --> 00:04:28,867
Okay.

85
00:04:31,233 --> 00:04:33,233
<i>Do you know who Sonny's boss is?</i>

86
00:04:33,733 --> 00:04:35,067
<i> No.</i>

87
00:04:35,200 --> 00:04:38,033
<i>Sonny's always careful
about his work.</i>

88
00:04:38,167 --> 00:04:39,433
But I wish...

89
00:04:39,567 --> 00:04:42,133
I did know who that bastard is.

90
00:04:42,267 --> 00:04:44,567
He should be accountable by the
law.

91
00:04:48,100 --> 00:04:50,467
Sir, how's Sonny doing?

92
00:04:53,567 --> 00:04:56,500
I'm sorry, Selena, but...

93
00:04:56,633 --> 00:04:58,467
Sonny's gone.

94
00:04:58,967 --> 00:05:00,833
What?

95
00:05:04,967 --> 00:05:09,800
I'm sorry.

96
00:05:10,867 --> 00:05:12,800
I told him...

97
00:05:12,933 --> 00:05:14,500
I told him...

98
00:05:34,700 --> 00:05:36,267
What do you think, Chief?

99
00:05:38,000 --> 00:05:41,467
Well, it seems like Selena
was telling the truth.

100
00:05:41,600 --> 00:05:44,267
She said she just wants justice,
for Sonny.

101
00:05:45,733 --> 00:05:47,033
Chief, you know,

102
00:05:47,167 --> 00:05:49,967
this case really feels like
a rabbit hole.

103
00:05:50,100 --> 00:05:51,367
Even Conde and the others

104
00:05:51,500 --> 00:05:53,033
are having a tough time
investigating.

105
00:05:53,167 --> 00:05:55,967
What really happened to Sonny?

106
00:05:59,900 --> 00:06:01,333
Rictus Grin.

107
00:06:02,600 --> 00:06:04,367
That creepy smile
Sonny had when he died...

108
00:06:04,500 --> 00:06:07,067
that's what it's called.

109
00:06:07,200 --> 00:06:09,233
There are only three
possible causes...

110
00:06:09,400 --> 00:06:10,667
First is tetanus.

111
00:06:10,800 --> 00:06:11,700
Then Wilson's disease.

112
00:06:11,833 --> 00:06:13,533
Both tested negative.

113
00:06:13,667 --> 00:06:15,367
Wait, what's the third?

114
00:06:15,933 --> 00:06:17,933
Strychnine poisoning.

115
00:06:18,433 --> 00:06:20,133
The test came back positive.

116
00:06:20,267 --> 00:06:22,200
Sonny was poisoned.

117
00:06:22,333 --> 00:06:23,933
Wait, that sounds familiar, Doc.

118
00:06:24,067 --> 00:06:25,867
Why, Sergeant Enriquez?

119
00:06:26,000 --> 00:06:28,267
Have you encountered
a similar case before?

120
00:06:28,400 --> 00:06:30,967
I saw it in an old film
of Amo, Sir.

121
00:06:31,600 --> 00:06:33,967
Smile of the Devil, 1987.

122
00:06:35,533 --> 00:06:37,467
This is the exact cause...

123
00:06:37,600 --> 00:06:39,533
of this frightening grin,

124
00:06:39,667 --> 00:06:43,467
also known as Rictus Grin.

125
00:06:43,633 --> 00:06:45,800
That's the third case, Doc.

126
00:06:47,733 --> 00:06:50,700
Looks like we have a serial
killer in this town.

127
00:06:50,833 --> 00:06:53,067
He is, Detective Santos.

128
00:06:53,200 --> 00:06:54,633
What I don't understand is,

129
00:06:54,767 --> 00:06:59,400
why is this criminal killing
this way?

130
00:07:03,567 --> 00:07:06,067
It only means one thing.

131
00:07:07,133 --> 00:07:09,100
What, Detective?

132
00:07:09,833 --> 00:07:13,733
This serial killer wants...

133
00:07:15,500 --> 00:07:19,600
to see his victims smiling.

134
00:07:23,100 --> 00:07:24,533
Hold on, hold on.

135
00:07:24,667 --> 00:07:25,367
I'm a fan of Amo too,

136
00:07:25,500 --> 00:07:28,933
but I don't remember that movie.

137
00:07:29,067 --> 00:07:30,733
It didn't really earn much.

138
00:07:30,867 --> 00:07:34,333
Well, movies are a far cry
from real life, right?

139
00:07:34,467 --> 00:07:37,733
And since strychnine poisoning
is rare,

140
00:07:37,867 --> 00:07:41,333
maybe this is something
worth looking into.

141
00:07:41,467 --> 00:07:44,467
Anyway, Chief,
here's my full report.

142
00:07:44,967 --> 00:07:47,267
Call me if you need
anything else.

143
00:07:47,400 --> 00:07:48,500
Thank you so much, Doc.

144
00:07:48,667 --> 00:07:50,633
Well, it's been a pleasure.

145
00:07:51,333 --> 00:07:53,667
Tonyo, if you want
to grab a drink,

146
00:07:53,800 --> 00:07:55,400
just text me, okay?

147
00:07:56,133 --> 00:07:57,633
Will do, Doc.

148
00:07:59,067 --> 00:08:01,500
All right, everyone,
let's go home.

149
00:08:01,633 --> 00:08:03,633
Oh, wait, Sir!

150
00:08:03,767 --> 00:08:05,100
Aren't we going
to talk about the...

151
00:08:05,233 --> 00:08:07,900
Sergeant, we'll talk
about that later.

152
00:08:09,400 --> 00:08:10,867
Let's go.

153
00:08:22,467 --> 00:08:23,633
Chief!

154
00:08:23,767 --> 00:08:25,333
Chief, wait!

155
00:08:27,333 --> 00:08:28,500
Is there something I don't know

156
00:08:28,633 --> 00:08:30,833
about the San Isidro case?

157
00:08:30,967 --> 00:08:36,200
Well, since you're here already,
Sergeant Enriquez,

158
00:08:36,333 --> 00:08:38,733
you explain it to Conde.

159
00:08:41,200 --> 00:08:42,300
Lieutenant Conde,

160
00:08:42,433 --> 00:08:44,767
I ran my own investigation

161
00:08:44,900 --> 00:08:45,700
and discovered a few things.

162
00:08:45,833 --> 00:08:49,933
First, the masks used
by the robbers

163
00:08:50,067 --> 00:08:52,133
were stolen from the museum,

164
00:08:52,267 --> 00:08:54,800
from Victor Santiago's
memorabilia collection.

165
00:08:54,967 --> 00:08:57,800
Second, the lines the robbers
used

166
00:08:57,933 --> 00:09:00,467
matched exactly with ones from
Amo's film.

167
00:09:00,600 --> 00:09:01,700
And third...

168
00:09:01,833 --> 00:09:03,933
Sonny's death?

169
00:09:04,567 --> 00:09:06,833
Also referenced
in his movie.

170
00:09:06,967 --> 00:09:08,867
That's strike three for Amo.

171
00:09:09,867 --> 00:09:13,467
You think he's involved?

172
00:09:13,933 --> 00:09:16,300
I can't say for sure.
But come on...

173
00:09:17,067 --> 00:09:18,300
isn't that a solid lead?

174
00:09:18,433 --> 00:09:20,000
It's worth pursuing.

175
00:09:22,200 --> 00:09:23,733
We can't just brush this off.

176
00:09:23,867 --> 00:09:25,367
What is this?
Another coincidence?

177
00:09:25,500 --> 00:09:27,933
All right, follow the lead,
Sergeant.

178
00:09:28,100 --> 00:09:29,400
But make sure

179
00:09:29,533 --> 00:09:31,167
Amo doesn't catch wind

180
00:09:31,300 --> 00:09:33,600
that we're investigating him.

181
00:09:34,200 --> 00:09:36,767
Because, I don't want
to look like a fool.

182
00:09:37,333 --> 00:09:38,833
Clear?

183
00:09:38,967 --> 00:09:40,633
Yes, Sir!

184
00:09:46,800 --> 00:09:48,367
Hello, Mayor?

185
00:09:49,300 --> 00:09:50,833
Yes, Sir.
I'll be right there.

186
00:10:00,967 --> 00:10:02,000
Enriquez!

187
00:10:02,133 --> 00:10:03,200
Bok, what's up?

188
00:10:03,333 --> 00:10:04,267
Come on, for the road.

189
00:10:05,133 --> 00:10:07,567
I'm sorry, Sir,
I'll head out first.

190
00:10:07,700 --> 00:10:09,067
All right?

191
00:10:12,600 --> 00:10:13,700
So, just us?

192
00:10:13,833 --> 00:10:15,300
Two bottles?

193
00:10:15,433 --> 00:10:16,600
Let's go.

194
00:10:16,733 --> 00:10:18,000
Bok...

195
00:10:19,400 --> 00:10:21,167
Did you know that there's
a Victor Santiago angle

196
00:10:21,300 --> 00:10:22,967
in this case we're handling?

197
00:10:23,100 --> 00:10:24,833
That one?
It's nothing, right?

198
00:10:25,233 --> 00:10:29,067
Didn't Enriquez mention
that before?

199
00:10:29,200 --> 00:10:33,067
About one of Amo's films.

200
00:10:33,200 --> 00:10:35,033
Chief didn't even pay attention
to that.

201
00:10:35,200 --> 00:10:36,933
Well, now he did.

202
00:10:37,067 --> 00:10:38,833
He gave Enriquez the go signal

203
00:10:38,967 --> 00:10:40,967
to follow that angle.

204
00:10:41,100 --> 00:10:42,100
Wait...

205
00:10:42,233 --> 00:10:44,000
what are you saying?

206
00:10:44,567 --> 00:10:46,967
Your dad's involved in this?

207
00:10:50,267 --> 00:10:52,433
How would I know?

208
00:10:53,333 --> 00:10:55,300
But if he is...

209
00:10:57,267 --> 00:10:59,800
I might not like
what I end up doing.

210
00:11:00,233 --> 00:11:01,967
You know what I think?

211
00:11:02,100 --> 00:11:07,500
We should just drink
and help you relax.

212
00:11:08,867 --> 00:11:09,900
Not now, Bok.

213
00:11:10,033 --> 00:11:11,667
I'm heading home.

214
00:11:13,767 --> 00:11:17,267
Bok, just one bottle,
and we will split it!

215
00:11:17,900 --> 00:11:19,933
Major! what do you mean...

216
00:11:20,067 --> 00:11:22,367
with all of you stationed at
this hospital,

217
00:11:22,500 --> 00:11:24,400
there's been zero progress in
the investigation

218
00:11:24,533 --> 00:11:25,967
on my daughter's kidnapping?!

219
00:11:26,100 --> 00:11:28,200
It's not like that, Mayor.

220
00:11:28,333 --> 00:11:30,400
We're following a lead...

221
00:11:30,533 --> 00:11:31,967
the strychnine.

222
00:11:32,100 --> 00:11:34,233
What, the poison that was used?

223
00:11:34,367 --> 00:11:35,833
Yes, Mayor.

224
00:11:36,767 --> 00:11:38,333
Please don't worry.

225
00:11:38,467 --> 00:11:40,100
We apologize,

226
00:11:40,233 --> 00:11:42,100
but please trust us...

227
00:11:42,267 --> 00:11:44,233
we're doing everything

228
00:11:44,367 --> 00:11:46,100
we can to get to the bottom

229
00:11:46,233 --> 00:11:48,533
of your daughter's
kidnapping.

230
00:11:48,667 --> 00:11:50,800
Just make sure

231
00:11:51,200 --> 00:11:53,033
we present the evidence to the
people

232
00:11:53,167 --> 00:11:55,333
before the elections!

233
00:11:55,467 --> 00:11:56,733
Got it?

234
00:11:56,867 --> 00:11:58,233
Yes, Mayor.

235
00:12:08,733 --> 00:12:10,333
Grandmother!

236
00:12:12,367 --> 00:12:13,400
Grandmother.

237
00:12:13,533 --> 00:12:15,367
Barbara...

238
00:12:15,833 --> 00:12:18,567
I thought you didn't live here
anymore.

239
00:12:18,700 --> 00:12:21,833
I thought I'd only have
Abdul and Mar for company.

240
00:12:21,967 --> 00:12:26,333
Oh, my grandmother missed me.

241
00:12:26,467 --> 00:12:28,067
You're happy, right?

242
00:12:28,200 --> 00:12:29,300
So, how are you?

243
00:12:29,433 --> 00:12:32,433
Have they caught the mastermind
behind the kidnapping yet?

244
00:12:33,300 --> 00:12:36,000
Not yet, but...

245
00:12:36,467 --> 00:12:39,700
finally, Grandmother,
Chief is now convinced

246
00:12:39,833 --> 00:12:42,267
by my theory that Amo
is connected to the case.

247
00:12:42,400 --> 00:12:45,800
Oh? So are you going to
investigate Amo now?

248
00:12:45,933 --> 00:12:47,933
Yes, but not officially.

249
00:12:48,100 --> 00:12:52,133
Chief said no one else
can know for now.

250
00:12:52,267 --> 00:12:54,700
So, Grandmother,
keep it quiet, okay?

251
00:12:55,433 --> 00:12:57,033
Of course.

252
00:12:58,500 --> 00:12:59,800
I'm happy for you.

253
00:12:59,933 --> 00:13:01,533
Thanks, Grandmother.

254
00:13:02,367 --> 00:13:04,567
Okay, we'll just go
change clothes first.

255
00:13:04,700 --> 00:13:06,167
Oh, wait a second...

256
00:13:06,900 --> 00:13:12,633
the coach from our village
basketball team came by.

257
00:13:12,767 --> 00:13:15,700
He asked me if you could be

258
00:13:15,833 --> 00:13:17,733
- muse for the basketball team.
- Oh no!

259
00:13:17,867 --> 00:13:20,367
Oh, those guys are
so persistent, Grandmother.

260
00:13:20,500 --> 00:13:22,667
I already told them
I don't want to be a muse!

261
00:13:22,833 --> 00:13:24,967
Why? Are you on duty that day?

262
00:13:25,100 --> 00:13:26,767
Not really, Grandmother.

263
00:13:26,900 --> 00:13:29,733
I just need to follow up some
leads.

264
00:13:29,867 --> 00:13:30,833
You know...

265
00:13:30,967 --> 00:13:33,467
I really don't want
to be a muse, Grandmother.

266
00:13:33,600 --> 00:13:34,933
What can we do?

267
00:13:35,067 --> 00:13:37,133
We are the only pretty
one around here.

268
00:13:37,267 --> 00:13:39,367
My beautiful granddaughter...

269
00:13:39,500 --> 00:13:40,833
Takes after her grandmother.

270
00:13:40,967 --> 00:13:42,133
Correct!

271
00:13:43,567 --> 00:13:45,267
Still, I don't want
to be a muse, Grandmother.

272
00:13:45,400 --> 00:13:46,933
- Okay?
- All right, fine.

273
00:13:47,067 --> 00:13:48,267
I'm gonna go shower.

274
00:13:48,400 --> 00:13:50,600
I'll just volunteer
myself instead.

275
00:13:58,867 --> 00:14:00,067
Hey!

276
00:14:00,633 --> 00:14:02,333
Hey! You're too loud!

277
00:14:02,967 --> 00:14:04,833
You're killing our buzz!

278
00:14:04,967 --> 00:14:06,333
Dude, what's your problem?

279
00:14:06,467 --> 00:14:07,967
You! Why?

280
00:14:13,300 --> 00:14:14,433
Cops!

281
00:14:14,567 --> 00:14:16,367
- Hey!
- Cops! Let's go, let's go!

282
00:14:16,800 --> 00:14:18,067
Cops, cops, hey!

283
00:14:18,200 --> 00:14:19,167
Hey! Hey, hey!

284
00:14:19,300 --> 00:14:21,033
- Grab them! Grab them!
- Hey, hey, hey, hey!

285
00:14:21,167 --> 00:14:22,200
Here!

286
00:14:22,333 --> 00:14:23,267
You guys, it's already late...

287
00:14:23,400 --> 00:14:25,067
and you're causing a ruckus in
our village!

288
00:14:25,200 --> 00:14:27,600
Oh! Still resisting, huh?

289
00:14:27,733 --> 00:14:29,500
- You're still resisting.
- Grab them!

290
00:14:29,667 --> 00:14:30,800
Hey! You, shut up!

291
00:14:30,933 --> 00:14:32,467
- Go to the village hall!
- Go to the village hall!

292
00:14:32,600 --> 00:14:33,667
You guys are so stubborn...

293
00:14:33,800 --> 00:14:34,900
it's already late!

294
00:14:35,033 --> 00:14:37,100
- Did anyone manage to get away?
- If we catch you again!

295
00:14:38,067 --> 00:14:39,067
What now, Amo?

296
00:14:39,200 --> 00:14:41,000
Visually impressive, right?

297
00:14:42,900 --> 00:14:44,300
Ugly, Director.

298
00:14:44,700 --> 00:14:46,367
Trash.

299
00:14:46,867 --> 00:14:49,900
I poured a lot of money
into your concept.

300
00:14:50,700 --> 00:14:53,533
I'll go bankrupt if this is the
kind of special effects

301
00:14:53,667 --> 00:14:55,900
we're showing people.

302
00:14:56,033 --> 00:14:57,900
Here's the deal, Director...

303
00:14:58,033 --> 00:14:59,967
the audience shouldn't feel like

304
00:15:00,100 --> 00:15:02,567
they're just watching a movie.

305
00:15:02,733 --> 00:15:05,200
Do you get what I'm saying?

306
00:15:06,467 --> 00:15:09,267
Okay, fine, fine.

307
00:15:18,067 --> 00:15:20,667
Amo, we've got a problem.

308
00:15:20,800 --> 00:15:22,900
What now?

309
00:15:26,000 --> 00:15:28,033
<i>Who's this actor-producer
now linked</i>

310
00:15:28,167 --> 00:15:29,767
<i>to the robbery
and kidnap-for-ransom?</i>

311
00:15:29,900 --> 00:15:31,400
<i>All the cases are money related.</i>

312
00:15:31,533 --> 00:15:32,800
<i> Probably running for office</i>

313
00:15:32,933 --> 00:15:34,900
<i>that's why he needs
a big budget.</i>

314
00:15:39,067 --> 00:15:42,600
I'm canceling your invite to the
league game tomorrow.

315
00:15:42,733 --> 00:15:44,933
I'll just set a press conference
instead.

316
00:15:45,067 --> 00:15:47,367
Huh? Why?

317
00:15:47,500 --> 00:15:51,400
Amo, we need to address this
already.

318
00:15:51,533 --> 00:15:54,333
It's affecting our poll results.

319
00:15:55,100 --> 00:15:58,033
Me? Victor Santiago...

320
00:15:58,167 --> 00:16:01,233
getting affected
by a blind item?

321
00:16:01,367 --> 00:16:03,367
I know it sounds
ridiculous, Amo.

322
00:16:04,767 --> 00:16:06,833
But nowadays,

323
00:16:06,967 --> 00:16:08,367
that's the battlefield.

324
00:16:08,533 --> 00:16:10,367
Image matters....

325
00:16:10,500 --> 00:16:13,167
especially on social media.

326
00:16:13,300 --> 00:16:15,167
I don't care.

327
00:16:15,300 --> 00:16:18,200
I'm still going to that
basketball league tomorrow.

328
00:16:18,333 --> 00:16:19,567
Thank you.

329
00:16:19,700 --> 00:16:21,767
- Good morning, Mayor!
- Good morning!

330
00:16:25,267 --> 00:16:27,133
Sophia, baby girl.

331
00:16:29,067 --> 00:16:30,500
You okay, sweetheart?

332
00:16:30,933 --> 00:16:32,800
Yes, Daddy.

333
00:16:32,933 --> 00:16:36,467
Sweetheart, Daddy and I need to
talk for a bit, okay?

334
00:16:38,767 --> 00:16:39,633
Excuse me, dear.

335
00:16:48,933 --> 00:16:50,267
Sophia.

336
00:16:50,400 --> 00:16:54,333
How's the investigation going on
Faye's kidnapping?

337
00:16:54,467 --> 00:16:56,300
No updates yet, but...

338
00:16:56,433 --> 00:16:59,633
they're following a lead now...

339
00:16:59,767 --> 00:17:03,233
that poison may have caused the
kidnapper's death.

340
00:17:04,333 --> 00:17:05,333
Do you have anything

341
00:17:05,467 --> 00:17:09,200
to do with that blind item
targeting Victor?

342
00:17:09,333 --> 00:17:10,967
Sophia...

343
00:17:11,100 --> 00:17:13,533
So that's really
what you think of me?

344
00:17:13,667 --> 00:17:15,633
Can you blame me?

345
00:17:16,367 --> 00:17:19,333
Joaquin, I'm just
reminding you...

346
00:17:19,467 --> 00:17:21,967
If you keep playing dirty,

347
00:17:22,100 --> 00:17:27,767
it will all bite back.

348
00:17:32,433 --> 00:17:33,800
sweetheart...

349
00:17:35,267 --> 00:17:36,867
sweetheart...

350
00:17:37,000 --> 00:17:39,500
Why is your face like that?

351
00:17:39,633 --> 00:17:42,600
Daddy, I'm still having
these nightmares.

352
00:17:44,700 --> 00:17:46,633
Don't worry, sweetheart.

353
00:17:46,767 --> 00:17:52,300
Rest assured, the police are
doing everything they can

354
00:17:52,467 --> 00:17:55,900
to make sure whoever's behind
this is held accountable.

355
00:17:57,533 --> 00:18:00,333
Sweetheart, let's leave Daddy
for now, sweetheart.

356
00:18:00,467 --> 00:18:02,500
He still has a lot to do.

357
00:18:04,267 --> 00:18:05,867
Thank you, Dad.

358
00:18:07,467 --> 00:18:08,433
Okay, sweetheart.

359
00:18:14,367 --> 00:18:15,267
<i> An actor-producer linked</i>

360
00:18:15,400 --> 00:18:16,733
<i>to robbery and
kidnap-for-ransom.</i>

361
00:18:16,867 --> 00:18:18,333
<i>All the cases are money-related</i>

362
00:18:18,467 --> 00:18:19,700
<i> Maybe he's running</i>

363
00:18:19,833 --> 00:18:21,933
<i>for office, that's why he needs
a big budget.</i>

364
00:18:23,967 --> 00:18:25,167
- That's it!
- You guys are lucky.

365
00:18:25,300 --> 00:18:26,100
We're checking out!

366
00:18:26,233 --> 00:18:27,733
thanks so much for
the vacation, Sir!

367
00:18:29,300 --> 00:18:30,567
Hurry up.

368
00:18:30,700 --> 00:18:31,533
Sir, you owe us, okay?

369
00:18:31,667 --> 00:18:32,800
Boss, thank you.

370
00:18:32,933 --> 00:18:35,700
I thought you forgot about us.

371
00:18:36,700 --> 00:18:38,833
Don't thank me.

372
00:18:38,967 --> 00:18:40,367
Thank her.

373
00:18:40,500 --> 00:18:41,533
Ma'am, thank you, really.

374
00:18:41,667 --> 00:18:43,233
- Thank you so much.
- Thank you so much.

375
00:18:43,367 --> 00:18:44,633
Ma'am, thank you.

376
00:18:44,767 --> 00:18:45,800
We're holding you to that debt,
okay?

377
00:18:45,933 --> 00:18:47,967
Don't forget.

378
00:18:48,100 --> 00:18:49,133
Yeah, yeah. All right already.
I got you.

379
00:18:49,267 --> 00:18:50,267
- Now go.
- Finally!

380
00:18:50,400 --> 00:18:53,000
- Let's drink!
- Leave.

381
00:18:53,133 --> 00:18:54,733
So noisy, these people.

382
00:18:54,900 --> 00:18:57,567
Enriquez, thank you.

383
00:18:58,333 --> 00:18:59,600
All good, Sir.

384
00:18:59,733 --> 00:19:01,567
I'll collect next time.

385
00:19:03,367 --> 00:19:04,667
Sir...

386
00:19:05,900 --> 00:19:08,000
I wanted to ask you something.

387
00:19:08,133 --> 00:19:10,133
I want to know what
you think about...

388
00:19:11,000 --> 00:19:13,533
Amo's connection to the cases
we're handling.

389
00:19:16,433 --> 00:19:17,300
I just want to understand

390
00:19:17,433 --> 00:19:20,767
why Amo's films are connected to
the case.

391
00:19:20,900 --> 00:19:22,600
Do you have any suggestions?

392
00:19:23,567 --> 00:19:25,767
Maybe you'd like to help me out?

393
00:19:26,733 --> 00:19:28,333
Enriquez!

394
00:19:29,133 --> 00:19:30,467
Sir.

395
00:19:31,400 --> 00:19:32,967
Have you seen this?

396
00:19:34,533 --> 00:19:36,167
<i>All the cases are money-related.</i>

397
00:19:36,300 --> 00:19:37,333
<i> Maybe he's running</i>

398
00:19:37,467 --> 00:19:39,667
<i> so he needs a huge budget.</i>

399
00:19:39,800 --> 00:19:41,600
Any idea where this came from?

400
00:19:42,200 --> 00:19:43,333
None, Sir.

401
00:19:43,467 --> 00:19:45,333
Don't move just yet

402
00:19:45,467 --> 00:19:48,400
to your investigation to Amo,
Enriquez.

403
00:19:50,933 --> 00:19:53,100
- But, Sir...
- Enriquez.

404
00:20:00,767 --> 00:20:02,433
- Mira.
- Yes, Chief?

405
00:20:02,600 --> 00:20:03,433
Before I forget,

406
00:20:03,567 --> 00:20:05,600
I'm assigning you to
the league...

407
00:20:05,733 --> 00:20:08,567
where Victor Santiago was
invited. Okay?

408
00:20:08,700 --> 00:20:11,100
Are you sure, Ma'am?

409
00:20:11,233 --> 00:20:12,000
Isn't that the one

410
00:20:12,133 --> 00:20:13,133
Amy's been dying to get into?

411
00:20:13,267 --> 00:20:14,467
That's my problem.

412
00:20:14,600 --> 00:20:16,667
Come on, just do your job.

413
00:20:17,667 --> 00:20:19,433
Thank you, Ma'am.

414
00:20:34,433 --> 00:20:36,200
Hey, Boss Tonyo!

415
00:20:36,367 --> 00:20:37,933
- Come eat with us!
- Sir Tonyo!

416
00:20:38,067 --> 00:20:39,500
Let's have a drink!

417
00:20:40,167 --> 00:20:41,033
Hi, Sir Tonyo!

418
00:20:41,167 --> 00:20:43,333
Hey, Apple, Peach,
how are you two?

419
00:20:43,467 --> 00:20:44,967
Still as gorgeous as ever.

420
00:20:45,100 --> 00:20:46,633
How's my baby Tonyo?

421
00:20:46,767 --> 00:20:48,367
Just your baby, Peach?

422
00:20:48,500 --> 00:20:51,067
Can't he be our Baby Tonyo?

423
00:20:53,467 --> 00:20:56,100
- I'm doing okay.
- But seriously, Sir Tonyo...

424
00:20:56,233 --> 00:20:58,233
if you need anything...

425
00:20:58,367 --> 00:20:59,500
just call us.

426
00:20:59,633 --> 00:21:04,133
Or if you want someone to
drink with, vent to about work

427
00:21:04,267 --> 00:21:05,300
we're just right here.

428
00:21:05,433 --> 00:21:07,367
Even if you need someone
to wash your underwear

429
00:21:07,500 --> 00:21:09,267
hey, hey!

430
00:21:09,767 --> 00:21:11,233
Don't go bugging Boss Tonyo.

431
00:21:11,367 --> 00:21:14,633
Boss Tonyo, all that stuff
they're saying to you right now?

432
00:21:14,767 --> 00:21:16,800
They've already told me all of
that too.

433
00:21:17,667 --> 00:21:21,367
And quit bothering him
about work.

434
00:21:21,500 --> 00:21:24,867
We don't talk about work when
there's alcohol around

435
00:21:25,000 --> 00:21:28,367
because this is a happy place.
Right, Boss Tonyo?

436
00:21:28,500 --> 00:21:30,133
Right, come on.

437
00:21:30,267 --> 00:21:33,133
Let's drink.
Let's drink! Let's drink!

438
00:21:33,267 --> 00:21:34,333
Let's drink and relax.

439
00:21:34,467 --> 00:21:36,200
Okay, just one, alright?

440
00:21:36,333 --> 00:21:38,967
Maybe you need a massage?

441
00:21:39,100 --> 00:21:41,333
Hey! Hey!

442
00:21:41,500 --> 00:21:42,867
Grandmother...

443
00:21:43,000 --> 00:21:44,400
Oh, my grandchild.

444
00:21:47,267 --> 00:21:49,500
I have a story for you.

445
00:21:49,633 --> 00:21:51,100
Earlier today,

446
00:21:51,233 --> 00:21:52,667
some kids almost

447
00:21:52,800 --> 00:21:56,200
got into a brawl again near
the market.

448
00:21:57,100 --> 00:22:01,267
It's not far off it could easily
turn into a real fight...

449
00:22:01,400 --> 00:22:03,333
those kids.

450
00:22:08,867 --> 00:22:10,467
What happened?

451
00:22:14,200 --> 00:22:15,967
Chief's ordering
the investigation on Amo's

452
00:22:16,133 --> 00:22:17,933
to be put on hold.

453
00:22:19,067 --> 00:22:22,467
Told me not to make any moves
until further notice.

454
00:22:23,333 --> 00:22:30,300
Because of that viral video.

455
00:22:38,800 --> 00:22:40,300
Grandchild...

456
00:22:41,267 --> 00:22:44,667
this is your favorite. I cooked
it for you.

457
00:22:52,167 --> 00:22:53,633
You can do this.

458
00:22:55,133 --> 00:22:56,833
Cry it out.

459
00:22:56,967 --> 00:22:57,800
You'll get through this.

460
00:23:34,833 --> 00:23:41,300
Can we talk for a moment, son?

461
00:23:43,500 --> 00:23:44,533
There's going to be
trouble later...

462
00:23:44,667 --> 00:23:46,800
- here in Barangay Sta. Fe.
- What kind of trouble?

463
00:23:46,933 --> 00:23:49,567
Boss, They said a gang war will
happen at the basketball court.

464
00:23:49,700 --> 00:23:50,500
What happened, Sir?

465
00:23:50,633 --> 00:23:51,333
Someone's being held hostage
inside.

466
00:23:51,467 --> 00:23:52,467
Check the perimeter

467
00:23:52,600 --> 00:23:55,167
and make sure the whole area's
under our control.

468
00:23:55,300 --> 00:23:57,133
Our mission is to make sure no
one else gets hurt.

469
00:23:57,300 --> 00:23:58,467
Hello, Conde? Where are you?

470
00:23:58,600 --> 00:23:59,900
We're following up on a lead

471
00:24:00,033 --> 00:24:01,000
about the poison, Sir.

472
00:24:01,133 --> 00:24:04,867
I can feel it, Sergeant Enriquez

473
00:24:05,000 --> 00:24:07,167
won't let go of his theory
about Amo.

474
00:24:07,300 --> 00:24:08,267
They look alike.

475
00:24:08,400 --> 00:24:10,467
I went to see him at
the convenience store.

476
00:24:10,600 --> 00:24:12,400
Then I just found him lying on
the floor.

477
00:24:12,533 --> 00:24:15,100
Unconscious. Beaten to a pulp.

478
00:24:15,233 --> 00:24:16,900
So I brought him home for now.

479
00:24:17,033 --> 00:24:19,433
I want a grandchild!

480
00:24:21,967 --> 00:24:23,500
Finally! Looks like she
surrenders herself to him!
